Make implicit-return-type lambdas in `is_color_terminal()` explicit.

ROCm 7.2.1's clang 18 is stricter than older clang releases when deducing
a lambda's implicit return type across multiple `return` statements and
rejects the lambdas in is_color_terminal() with:

  error: return type 'bool' must match previous return type 'int' when
         lambda expression has unspecified explicit return type

Spelling the return type explicitly (`-> bool`) fixes the diagnostic.

--- a/include/spdlog/details/os-inl.h
+++ b/include/spdlog/details/os-inl.h
@@ -404,7 +404,7 @@
     return true;
 #else
 
-    static const bool result = []() {
+    static const bool result = []() -> bool {
         const char *env_colorterm_p = std::getenv("COLORTERM");
         if (env_colorterm_p != nullptr) {
             return true;
@@ -419,7 +419,7 @@
             return false;
         }
 
-        return std::any_of(terms.begin(), terms.end(), [&](const char *term) {
+        return std::any_of(terms.begin(), terms.end(), [&](const char *term) -> bool {
             return std::strstr(env_term_p, term) != nullptr;
         });
     }();
